               <p>JAMES KALMAN. I am a <rs id="t18300415-340-viclabel1839" type="occupation">labourer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-340-victim2815 t18300415-340-viclabel1839"></join>. On the 7th of April, between eleven and twelve o'clock in the day, I was in the street with a tin box in my side-pocket, containing two sovereigns and 9s. - as I crossed the street from a coach, there was a crowd, and before I could get in among the crowd, I felt a hand at my pocket and missed my box; it was picked up with nothing in it but a ticket - I took the prisoner's hand out of my pocket; he ran off - I followed him, and he was taken without getting out of my sight; I did not see him throw the box down.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-340-person2816">
                  JOHN 
                  FORRESTER
               <interp inst="t18300415-340-person2816" type="surname" value="FORRESTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-340-person2816" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-340-person2816" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. On the 7th of April, I saw the prisoner running very hard and looking very agitated - the prosecutor was behind him calling Stop thief! I said, "What have you lost?" he said a tin box - I called out, Stop him! and a man stopped him: two more ran away down Old Gravel-lane, behind Houndsditch, and the box was found thrown over a yard in that direction.(Box produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. When I was taken I was quite round another street - several people were running.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18300415-340-verdict1840" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300415-340-verdict1840" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 23. - <rs id="t18300415-340-punish1841" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300415-340-punish1841" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-340-defend2813 t18300415-340-punish1841"></join>
               Transported for Life
